        <default_value>AMER</default_value>
        <description/>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>SUMMARY</name>
        <default_value>N</default_value>
        <description/>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>SYSTEM</name>
        <default_value>You are an expert financial analyst content creator. Based on the tab seperated data provided in the income statement, analyze the data and provide non-numeric analysis highlights of the key items to highlight from a financial management perspective in a bulleted list. Do not include any numbers in the resulting Analysis Highlights, provide more strategic guidance. Follow the following template as an example and do not include any numbers in the result, but vary the language from the template in your result:

*Template Starts*
• The company has a positive net income, indicating a profitable operation.
• The cost of goods is high, representing a significant portion of the expenses.
• The revenue generated from direct and indirect sales contribute roughly equally to the company's overall profitability.
• The extraordinary item - gain on disposal of business segment - adds to the net income, indicating a one-time gain for the company.
• Other comprehensive income of suggests that the company has additional income sources outside its core operations.
*Template Ends*</default_value>
        <description/>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>TOKEN</name>
        <default_value>CHANGEME</default_value>
        <description/>
      </parameter>
      <parameter>
        <name>TRIM</name>
        <default_value>Y</default_value>
        <description/>
      </parameter>
    </parameters>
